On December 12, 2019, the President signed into law several bills that designate certain facilities of the United States Postal Service with new names. The bills include: 

1. H.R. 887: It designates the facility of the United States Postal Service in Orem, Utah, as the Jerry C. Washburn Post Office Building.
2. H.R. 1252: It designates the facility of the United States Postal Service in Van Nuys, California, as the Marilyn Monroe Post Office.
3. H.R. 1253: It designates the facility of the United States Postal Service in Pacoima, California, as the Ritchie Valens Post Office Building.
4. H.R. 1526: It designates the facility of the United States Postal Service in Tumwater, Washington, as the Eva G. Hewitt Post Office.
5. H.R. 1844: It designates the facility of the United States Postal Service in Elgin, Illinois, as the Corporal Alex Martinez Memorial Post Office Building.